            <thetext>IMPORTANT: This issue is present in Chrome 7.0.517.0, *NOT* Chrome 6. Chrome 7 isnt&#39;t listed in Bugzilla yet.

Chrome 7 has a bug where CSS background images will not be loaded if they are referenced using relative paths *and* the style definition is applied using innerHTML:

http://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=54983

Until this bug is fixed, widgets using qx.ui.decoration.css3.BorderImage will have no background image.</thetext>
